    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>Clarendon Congregational Church was organized in 1880. Rev. Samuel Dana Hosmer was the
        first acting pastor from September 1879 to his resignment in April of 1882. Rev. Hosmer
        graduated from Harvard in 1850 and Andover Newton Theological School in 1856. Clarendon
        Congregational Church incorporated in 1890. In 1930, the church celebrated its 50th
        anniversary by unveiling a stained-glass window titled "The Transfiguration". This artwork
        was inspired by the 12th century windows of the same name that resides in the Cath√©drale de
        Chartres, France. The Clarendon Congregational Church dissolved circa 1964.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection houses administrative records from the Clarendon Congregational Church in
        Hyde Park Boston, Massachusetts. The collection includes church records, meeting minutes,
        church school meeting minutes as well as scrapbooks containing various programs, orders of
        service, circulars, and photographs.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>Materials have been arranged in chronological order by start date.</p>
    </arrangement>
